Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.00,0:00:26.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs100\t(,\fs110)\frz1\fad(3000,500)\fsp0\fscx120\pos(960,800)\b0\shad0\bord0}地          球          脉          动
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.06,0:00:44.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们星球上1/3的陆地是沙漠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A third of the land on our planet is desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.90,0:00:57.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些地球脸上的大伤疤看似毫无生机\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These great scars on the face of the Earth appear to be lifeless,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.66,0:01:00.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而令人吃惊的是并非如此\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but surprisingly none are.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.10,0:01:12.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在所有沙漠中 生命总能以某些方式闪现\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In all of them life manages somehow to keep a precarious hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.75,0:01:18.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs125\fsp7.5\fad(1000,1000)\pos(958,920)}奇    幻    沙    漠
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.00,0:01:39.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs60\fsp5\fad(1000,1000)\pos(960,1080)\bord0\shad3}画 外 音\N{\fs90}大卫 · 爱登堡   爵士
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.02,0:01:35.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沙漠并非都是炎热的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Not all deserts are hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.86,0:01:39.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,西伯利亚的寒风以50英里的时速\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Fifty-mile-an-hour winds blowing in from Siberia
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.42,0:01:43.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,夹杂着风雪横扫蒙古戈壁沙漠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}bring snow to the Gobi Desert in Mongolia.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.10,0:02:11.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然夏季气温高达50℃\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}From a summer high of 50 degrees centigrade
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.62,0:02:15.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是到了冬至却能降至零下40℃\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the temperature in midwinter can drop to minus 40,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.74,0:02:19.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使得这里成为一片最荒凉的沙漠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}making this one of the harshest deserts of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.18,0:02:33.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只有少许动物能适应 这种极端的气候变化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Few animals can survive these extreme changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.10,0:02:41.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,野双峰驼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Wild Bactrian camels,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.54,0:02:44.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一种地球上最稀有的哺乳动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}one of the rarest mammals on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.26,0:02:46.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能也是最坚韧的动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And perhaps the hardiest.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.98,0:02:50.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们最大的困难莫过于缺水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their biggest problem is the lack of water,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.58,0:02:52.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尤其是现在——冬天\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}particularly now, in winter,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.26,0:02:55.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里仅有的一点水也结成了冰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}when the little there is is locked up as ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.34,0:03:06.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,奇怪的是 这里的雪永远都不会融化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Surprisingly, snow here never melts.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.50,0:03:11.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,又冷又干的空气使它们无法解冻\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The air is just too cold and too dry for it to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.14,0:03:19.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阳光把它们直接变成了水蒸气\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The sun's rays turn it straight into vapour.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.74,0:03:21.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们升华了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It evaporates.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.34,0:03:32.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是这是唯一的水源\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But it is the only source of water,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.62,0:03:35.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以双峰驼只能吃雪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so Bactrian camels eat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.30,0:03:37.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在世界上其它地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Elsewhere in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.74,0:03:43.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一只骆驼找到水坑后  能一次喝下200升水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}a camel at a waterhole can drink as much as 200 litres during a single visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.02,0:03:49.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但在这里的饮水策略却是少而频繁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Here the strategy is to take little and often.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.50,0:03:50.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这当然有充分的理由\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And with good reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.98,0:03:54.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为肚子里装满雪将是致命的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for filling the stomach with snow could be fatal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.94,0:04:05.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,骆驼必须限定自己 每天只能吃10升左右的雪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The camels must limit themselves to the equivalent of just 10 litres a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.70,0:04:24.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冬季是交配时节\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Winter is the time for breeding.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.94,0:04:36.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种奇怪的表演是公双峰驼 吸引路过的母骆驼的一种方式\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This extraordinary performance is a male Bactrian camel's way of attracting the attention of a passing female.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.54,0:04:42.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在夏天 骆驼不能远离水坑\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In summer the camels can't stray far from waterholes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.30,0:04:46.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是现在 遍地都是唾手可得的雪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But now, with mouthfuls of snow lying everywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.62,0:04:50.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们便能长途跋涉寻找配偶\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they can travel widely in search of mates.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.82,0:04:59.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,今天 这些沙漠专家的 野生数量已不足1000只\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Today less than a thousand of these desert specialists remain in the wild.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.06,0:05:04.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,戈壁尽管环境险恶 却是它们最后的据点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Gobi, hostile though it is, is their last stronghold.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.30,0:05:14.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,别的沙漠都和戈壁不太一样\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There's no other desert quite like the Gobi,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.66,0:05:17.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么这里会成为沙漠呢\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but why is this place a desert?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.82,0:05:21.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里有一个简单而又重要的原因\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There is one simple and massive cause -
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.94,0:05:23.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喜马拉雅山脉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the Himalayas.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.90,0:05:31.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从南方过来的暖湿气流 撞上了这面巨大的屏障\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Clouds blowing from the south hit this gigantic barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.98,0:05:33.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在被迫抬升的过程中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As they're forced upwards
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.46,0:05:36.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,水汽在山坡上逐渐凝结\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so they empty their moisture on the mountain slopes,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.82,0:05:40.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只有一小部分到达另一边的土地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}leaving little for the land on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.86,0:05:49.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从太空中看 沙漠非常显眼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}From the space deserts are very conspicuous.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.30,0:05:56.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,绵延数百英里的沙丘像是一条条皱边花纹\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Dunes of sand hundreds of miles long streak their surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.66,0:06:03.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于没有植被覆盖\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With no cloak of vegetation to conceal them
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.82,0:06:08.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,赤裸的岩石显露出奇特的造型\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}strange formations are exposed in the naked rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.82,0:06:17.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非洲的撒哈拉沙漠是世界上最大的沙漠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Africa's Sahara is the largest desert of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.50,0:06:19.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的面积相当于美国\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's the size of the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.86,0:06:24.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也是全世界最大的沙尘源\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the biggest source of sand and dust in the entire world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.14,0:07:06.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如此巨大的沙暴出现时毫无征兆\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Sandstorms like these appear without warning
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.46,0:07:11.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所到之处能见度骤降为零  几天内横扫的地区比英国还大\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and reduce visibility for days over areas the size of Britain.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.90,0:07:25.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,单峰驼——只有一个肉峰的骆驼  顶着沙暴大步行走\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Dromedaries, single-humped camels, take these storms in their stride.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.38,0:07:32.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最重的沙子只能离开地面几米\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The heaviest sand rises only a few metres above the ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.78,0:07:37.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是尘埃却能被吹上5000多米高的天空\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the dust can be blown 5,000 metres up into the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.94,0:07:46.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,夹杂着沙粒的强风\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The ferocious wind, armed with grains of sand,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.70,0:07:49.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,塑造了各种沙漠地形\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is the agent that shapes all deserts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.18,0:08:05.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爬行动物的皮肤覆盖着鳞甲  能抵御刺痛的沙粒\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Reptiles have armoured scaly skins that protect them from the stinging grains.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.94,0:08:12.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而昆虫则得遭受猛烈“炮火”的轰击\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For insects the bombardment can be very severe indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.62,0:08:17.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,唯一的藏身之处当然是在沙子下面\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The only escape is below the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.94,0:08:38.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着风的起落、侵蚀和旋绕\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the winds rise and fall, swallow and eddy
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.14,0:08:41.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沙子被堆成了一座座沙丘\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so they pile the sand into dunes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.06,0:08:49.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些沙漠布景可宽达数百英里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These sand scenes can be hundreds of miles across.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.10,0:08:57.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在纳米比亚 风塑造了 一些世界上最大的沙丘\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In Namibia the winds have built some of the biggest dunes in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.22,0:09:09.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些巨型沙丘高达300多米\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Star dunes like these can be 300 metres high.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.46,0:09:13.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,斜坡上吹起的沙粒 在沙丘顶部的边棱处飞扬\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Grains, swept up the flanks, are blown off the crests of the ridges
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.02,0:09:16.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以沙丘移动的部分只是顶部\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so it's only the tops that are moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.34,0:09:29.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些沙丘的主体 可能已有5000多年未曾移动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The main body of these dunes may not have shifted for 5,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.30,0:09:46.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,岩石很难抵挡风沙持续不断的摧残\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Few rocks can resist the continuous blast of the sand carrying wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.62,0:09:50.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些石头如今矗立在埃及的白色沙漠中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These outcrops are standing in Egypt's White Desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.70,0:09:54.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它们也坚持不了多久\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But they will not do so for much longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.10,0:10:01.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们正被无情地凿碎 变成更多的沙粒\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're being inexorably chiseled away and turned into more sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.14,0:10:46.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在 这些严重侵蚀的石块 已被放逐在沙海之中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now lumps of heavily eroded rocks have been marooned in a sea of sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.38,0:11:06.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些高达100多米的锯齿般的石锥\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These jagged pyramids a hundred metres tall
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.14,0:11:09.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,曾经是一整块岩石高地的一部分\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}were once part of a continuous rocky plateau.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.74,0:11:13.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,强悍的风沙最终将使它们完全消失\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The blasting sand will eventually eliminate them altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.14,0:11:28.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,风的无情力量总是使沙漠的面貌不断改变\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The relentless power of the wind ensures that the face of a desert is continually changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.34,0:11:31.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是有一样东西永远都会存在\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But there is one constant presence -
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.10,0:11:41.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沙漠的太阳\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the desert sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.06,0:11:58.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳的热力使水蒸发\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The sun's heat and power to evaporate water
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.62,0:12:04.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这对所有生活在这里的动物的 身体和习性都有极其深远的影响\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}has had a profound effect on the bodies and habits of everything that lives here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.14,0:12:11.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这里 太阳将会成为杀手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This sun potentially is a killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.86,0:12:16.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,红大袋鼠必须意识到这一点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And the red kangaroos must acknowledge that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.82,0:12:19.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此时 太阳还未升起\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Right now, while the sun is low,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.02,0:12:22.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并没有直接危及到生命\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}there's no immediate cause for concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.78,0:12:26.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是这种情况不会持续多久\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But this situation won't last long.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.62,0:12:33.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,澳大利亚是世界上最干旱的大陆  整个白天酷热难当\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Australia is the world's most arid continent with blistering daytime temperatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.54,0:12:46.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每过一小时 气温就将升高5℃\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Every hour the temperature rises by five degrees centigrade.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.70,0:12:56.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,热度很快就会达到临界点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Soon the heat will reach a critical point.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.02,0:13:11.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,任何一只呆在外面的袋鼠 都将面临中暑的威胁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Any kangaroo out in the open is in serious danger of overheating.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.10,0:13:23.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,待到阳光最毒辣之时  地面温度已升高至70℃\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the full sun the temperature on the ground soars to 70 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.46,0:13:33.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到了正午 太阳的炙焰 迫使它们不得不寻找庇荫处\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}By midday the radiation is so intense they must take shelter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.50,0:13:55.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在树荫下 它们虽然避开了太阳的能量\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the shade they're shielded from much of the sun's energy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.98,0:13:59.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它们的体温仍在升高\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but their body temperature can still rise.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.50,0:14:05.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以它们将唾液抹在前臂上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So they lick saliva on to their forearms
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.06,0:14:09.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里的血管网比较贴近皮肤表层\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}where there is a network of blood vessels close to the surface of the skin
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.10,0:14:14.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此 当唾液蒸发时 血液也能得到冷却\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and, as the saliva evaporates, their blood is cooled.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.14,0:14:20.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这幅热影像能证明这种方法非常有效\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This thermal image shows just how effective the process is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.78,0:14:24.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,身上蓝色的部分是较冷的部位\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The blue areas on the body are the cooler parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.18,0:14:36.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,唾液干了之后还得重新抹上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the saliva dries it has to be replaced
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.90,0:14:41.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,袋鼠真正排放出去的体液也就是这些\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and this is a real drain on the kangaroo's body fluids.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.02,0:14:54.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使是在树荫下 土地照样被烤得火热\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Even in the shade the earth is baking hot
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.34,0:14:58.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,于是袋鼠刨去灼烫的表层沙土\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so the kangaroos dig away the warmed topsoil
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.86,0:15:01.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,贴近下面较冷的地面\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to get at the cooler ground beneath.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.62,0:15:28.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通过呆在树荫下  并利用舔唾液的方法控制体温\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}By staying in the shade and licking to control their body temperature
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.22,0:15:31.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,袋鼠便能熬过一天中最热的时段\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}kangaroos manage to get through the hottest part of the day
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.30,0:15:32.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而不至于中暑\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}without heat stroke.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.98,0:15:36.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是对于大多数沙漠动物来说\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But for the majority of desert animals
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.30,0:15:39.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,光凭这些手段还不足以在此生存\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}this strategy would not be enough for survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.86,0:16:06.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非洲的耳廓狐长有奇特的大耳  它们能散发热量\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The extraordinary ears of the fennec foxes of Africa radiate heat
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.78,0:16:09.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过动物也有其它保持凉爽的方法\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the animals have another way of keeping cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.38,0:16:21.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们白天呆在地下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They spend their days underground
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.82,0:16:24.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直到日落之后才会出现\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and only emerge at sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.30,0:16:39.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,夜晚的情况变得很不一样\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Darkness brings huge changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.66,0:16:44.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在撒哈拉沙漠中  晚上的气温会下降整整30℃\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the Sahara the temperature can drop as much as 30 degrees during the night,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.50,0:16:49.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在如此凉爽的时候  小耳廓狐也能尽情玩耍\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so it's cool enough to allow these desert fox cubs to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.26,0:16:58.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此时各种各样的动物都开始现身\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}All sorts of creatures now appear
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.90,0:17:02.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,包括一些意想不到的动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}including some really unexpected ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.98,0:17:07.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蟾蜍长着透水的皮肤\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Toads have permeable skins
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.14,0:17:10.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,若是在白天的高温下  它们很快就会因为脱水而死\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and would quickly die from desiccation out in the daytime heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.06,0:17:13.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以只有到了晚上它们才能离开庇护所\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's only now that they can leave shelter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.54,0:17:18.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蝎子也是同样的情况\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The same is true for scorpions,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.46,0:17:21.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管它们的外壳其实并不透水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}even though their shells are actually watertight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.70,0:17:37.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上 大多数小型沙漠动物 都是夜行动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In fact, most small desert creatures are nocturnal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.46,0:17:43.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以只有此时你才能判断 沙漠中究竟有多少生物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so it's only now that you can judge just how much life there can be in the desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.70,0:17:49.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是水分在晚上也会损耗  必须在什么时候想办法补充\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But moisture, lost even at night, has to be replaced sometime somehow
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.38,0:17:53.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这一问题支配着所有沙漠动物的生活\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and that problem dominates the lives of all desert dwellers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.10,0:18:04.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,智利的阿塔卡马沙漠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Atacama in Chile.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.34,0:18:07.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里是世界上最干旱的沙漠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is the driest desert in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.30,0:18:12.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有的地方可能连续5年不会下一滴雨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Some parts may not see rain for fifty years
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.26,0:18:13.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,既然有了这一纪录\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and with such a record
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.74,0:18:17.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不难想象这个地方定是彻底的荒芜\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}you'd expect the place to be completely barren.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.18,0:18:26.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些是南美洲的骆驼——原驼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These are South America's camels, guanacos.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.78,0:18:30.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们非常善于保存水分\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're very good at conserving moisture
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.06,0:18:33.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它们仍须定期补充水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but they nonetheless need a regular supply of water.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.86,0:18:49.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中一部分水取自仙人掌花\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They get it partly from cactus flowers
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.10,0:18:52.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但这里又牵扯出另一个问题\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but that explanation raises another question.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.78,0:18:58.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,仙人掌为何能在这个无雨地带生存\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}How do the cacti survive without rain?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.74,0:19:09.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,热浪抽干了地面上所有的水分\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Hot winds suck all the moisture from the surface of the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.18,0:19:16.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,显然 这里必须有其它东西 能代替雨水的作用\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Clearly there must be something else that takes the place of rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.34,0:19:23.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,答案就是一股与陆地平行的寒冷洋流\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The secret is a cold sea current that runs parallel to the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.42,0:19:42.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冷水使得上方的暖湿气流冷却\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The cold water cools the moist warm air above it
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.70,0:19:45.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,形成一团团的雾霾\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and that produces banks of fog.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.98,0:20:14.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与此同时 吹向海岸的风将雾气带上陆地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At the same time wind blowing on to the shore sweeps the fog inland.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.06,0:20:33.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不久之后 雾凝结成了露水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Before long the cacti are dripping with dew.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.98,0:20:43.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雾经常会出现\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The fog is so regular
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.90,0:20:47.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就连喜湿的地衣也能在仙人掌上生长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that moisture loving lichens are able to grow on the cacti
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.38,0:20:50.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们像海绵一样吸收着水汽\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they absorb liquid like a sponge.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.02,0:20:55.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在一个几乎没有雨的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the land of almost no rain
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.66,0:21:01.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些宝贵的水滴是许多动物的救命物资\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}these precious drops are life-savers for many different creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.58,0:21:15.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在更远的内陆地区  空气一直十分灼热 水汽无法凝结\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Further inland the air remains so warm that its moisture does not condense
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.30,0:21:22.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此这个狭长地带实际上是 阿塔卡马沙漠中唯一的生命绿洲\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so this slender strip of desert is virtually the only part of the Atacama where life can exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.86,0:21:27.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果没有雾\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Without the fog,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.02,0:21:31.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这片土地也将成为不毛之地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}this land, too, would be empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.74,0:21:47.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,原驼尽量舔吮露水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The guanacos make the most of the dew
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.18,0:21:49.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它们不会保留多久\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but it will not remain for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.34,0:21:53.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,1～2小时后 太阳将使它们蒸发\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In an hour or two the sun will have burnt it off
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.18,0:21:56.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,仙人掌表面将回复干燥\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and dry the surface of the cacti.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.26,0:22:09.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,亚利桑那州的索诺兰沙漠 并不像阿塔卡马沙漠那样干旱\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Sonoran desert in Arizona is not quite so dry as the Atacama -
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.58,0:22:11.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里有时会下一些雨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}some rain does fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.58,0:22:14.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是降雨次数很少\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But it is infrequent
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.26,0:22:15.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦雨水到来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and when it does arrive
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.78,0:22:19.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有动植物都必须 做好准备尽量地利用它们\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}animals and plants have to be ready to make the most of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.94,0:22:22.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要下雨了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And it's coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.94,0:22:33.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当夏季季风吹来时\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}When the summer monsoon blows in
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.06,0:22:36.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,巨大的弁庆柱 ——一种世界上最大的仙人掌\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the giant saguaros, one of the biggest of all cacti,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.54,0:22:39.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,准备充分利用雨水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}are ready to take full advantage of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.10,0:23:17.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,暴风雨过后 弁庆柱 用又长又浅的根系吸收水分\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}After a rainstorm the saguaro's long shallow root system sucks up the water
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.66,0:23:23.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,茎上的皱褶使之能迅速膨胀\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the pleats on its trunk enable it to expand rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.94,0:23:36.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,吸饱水后 弁庆柱的茎干中 已储存了5吨左右的水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}When full, a saguaro stem can store up to five tonnes of water
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.26,0:23:40.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这足以帮助它们度过几个月的旱季\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and that's enough to see it through many months of drought.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.66,0:23:50.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些立柱般的巨型植物 为橙腰啄木鸟提供了住所\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The trunks of these huge plants provide homes for the gila woodpecker.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.14,0:23:58.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过鸟并非唯一从仙人掌那里 获得好处的动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But birds are not the only animals to benefit from the presence of the cacti.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.18,0:24:16.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在夏季的4个星期里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}During four weeks of the summer
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.14,0:24:21.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,弁庆柱在晚上开花 吸引了不少拜访者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the saguaros bloom at night to attract visitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.54,0:24:27.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些花中装满了花粉和花蜜\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The pollen and nectar with which these flowers are loaded
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.82,0:24:31.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,吸引了长鼻蝠和长舌蝠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}attract long-nosed and long-tongued bats.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.54,0:24:51.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蝙蝠数日前离开墨西哥以躲避酷暑\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The bats left Mexico a few days earlier to escape the heat of summer
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.62,0:24:55.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正向北飞往美国南部\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and are on their way north to the southern United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.46,0:25:01.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要想到达那里  它们必须穿越索诺兰沙漠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}To get there, they have to cross the Sonoran desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.06,0:25:09.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过这片沙漠很大\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But the desert is so big
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.02,0:25:12.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们一年中大部分时间都无法穿越这里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that for most of the year they would be unable to cross it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.74,0:25:15.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在 有了正在开花的弁庆柱\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now, with the saguaro in bloom,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.14,0:25:18.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们便能在旅途中得到休整\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they can refuel on the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.26,0:25:31.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看来弁庆柱进化出的 这种成功的储水方式\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So the saguaro's success in developing a way to store water
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.22,0:25:37.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如今已关系到大部分 在此生活和旅行的动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is now crucial to most of the animals that live or even travel through this land.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.02,0:26:20.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,缺少雨水的环境塑造了这些沙漠中的图标\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The scarcity of rain determined the shape of this icon of the desert
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.54,0:26:26.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管水很少 但它也和风一样  造就了各种地形\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but water, scarce thought it is, has also, like the wind, shaped the land itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.22,0:26:45.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在犹他州的沙漠中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the deserts of Utah
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.14,0:26:50.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,古老的河流冲开岩壁 不断拓宽这些峡谷\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}ancient rivers flowing across sandstone country steadily widen their canyons
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.62,0:26:56.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直到把其间的土地削凿成 今天这样的尖峰和石塔\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}until now the land between them has been reduced to spires and pinnacles.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.26,0:27:30.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于几乎没有土壤保留地表水分\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With little or no soil to retain the water on the surface of the land
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.34,0:27:33.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里的生物极其稀少\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}life here is scarce indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.98,0:27:37.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当资源有限的时候\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And when resources are limited,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.06,0:27:39.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冲突自然不可避免\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}conflict is never far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.74,0:27:52.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些是努比亚羱羊\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These are Nubian ibex
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.38,0:27:54.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们正摆好架势准备激战\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they are squaring up for a duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.06,0:28:02.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冲突一旦爆发\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And when trouble starts,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.54,0:28:07.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,聪明的羱羊很清楚 最好的战术就是占领制高点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}a smart ibex knows that the best thing to do is to gain higher ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.54,0:28:27.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些其实是次级别的公羱羊\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These are actually subordinate male ibex,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.86,0:28:30.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它们的战斗依然十分激烈\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but their fights are nonetheless serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.34,0:28:34.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,失败一次或许意味着将永远失去生育权\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Losing one might mean never getting the chance to breed ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.82,0:29:00.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同级别的参赛者在此公平竞争\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}When competitors are evenly matched as they are here,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.34,0:29:03.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,决斗会持续一小时左右\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}duels can last for an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.10,0:29:26.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,高温下的战斗确实很耗费体力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In this heat the effort is trully exhausting.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.10,0:29:34.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是这里的获胜者会获得重要的排名  一步步到达公羊排行榜的第一位\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But victory here will gain important ranking points on a male's way to the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.34,0:30:05.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这类决斗非常危险\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There's so much at stake
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.94,0:30:08.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且并不总是公平的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that not all play fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.90,0:30:25.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这场战斗已经分出了胜负\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The battle has produced the winner,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.22,0:30:29.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是最后的奖品仍然不属于它\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the ultimate prize is not his yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.54,0:30:36.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它通常属于拥有统治权的公羊\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}That currently belongs to the dominant male ibex.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.70,0:30:42.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的地位为它赢得了一群忠诚的母羊\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}His rank earns him the loyalty of a harem of females
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.66,0:30:46.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们一起紧跟着它穿越沙漠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they follow him closely as he travels across this desert
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.26,0:30:48.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,寻找水和食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}searching for foof and water.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.50,0:30:53.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它不必浪费时间寻找配偶\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He doesn't have to waste time looking for mates -
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.50,0:30:55.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们都是它的妻子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they're his for the taking,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.14,0:30:59.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以它要做的只是保证它们健康精壮\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so he can concentrate with them on keeping fit and healthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.62,0:31:17.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蜥蜴是沙漠专家\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Lizards are desert specialists.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.54,0:31:23.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这里 它们的数量多得惊人\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But here, their numbers are extraordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.42,0:31:35.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非洲南部的这些岩缝中 容纳着世界上最大的蜥蜴群\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These crevices in South Africa contain the highest density of lizards in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.86,0:31:48.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们叫做扁石蜥——因为显而易见的原因\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're called flat lizards for obvious reasons,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.38,0:31:53.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们炫耀自己五颜六色的腹部 是为了争夺领地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they flaunt their multi-coloured bellies in territorial disputes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.66,0:31:57.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它赢了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He's made his point,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.30,0:32:00.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在该是寻找食物的时候了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and now it's time to find some food.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.78,0:32:03.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着白天气温的升高\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the day warms up,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.38,0:32:05.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蜥蜴离开它们藏身的岩缝\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the lizards move away from their cracks
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.54,0:32:07.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,奔向峡谷底部\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and head down to the bottom of the gorge.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.42,0:32:11.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的目标是这条小河\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their goal is the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.86,0:32:16.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,河边没有一点食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There is no food at the edge,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.18,0:32:19.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是这条沙漠河流却藏着一个秘密\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but this desert river holds a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.98,0:32:31.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每天 成千上万的蚋从奔腾的河水中羽化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Each day blackfly rise from turbulent stretches of the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.50,0:32:33.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是蜥蜴到此的目的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is what the lizards have come for.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.74,0:32:50.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蚋不会降落\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The black fly never land,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.82,0:32:54.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以蜥蜴必须跳起来捕食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so the lizards have to leap for their food.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.18,0:33:11.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每只身怀绝技的小蜥蜴 一天能吃掉50多只小虫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In one day each of these acrobatic little lizards may catch 50 flies.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.10,0:33:27.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管已有几百只蜥蜴在此捕猎  这里仍聚集着无数飞虫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are plenty of flies to go round, even with hundreds of lizards competing for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.14,0:33:47.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在远离这些急流的地方  扁石蜥的数量则要少得多\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Away from these rapids flat lizard populations are found much smaller numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.10,0:33:52.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但在这里 一种特别的资源 带动了另一物种的兴起\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But here one unusual abundance has produced another.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.62,0:34:05.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沙漠的形成是因为缺少水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Deserts are created by the lack of water,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.50,0:34:09.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是这里杀死动物的 真正原因并非炎热和缺水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but what actually kills animals here is not heat or thirst,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.94,0:34:11.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而是缺少食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but lack of food.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.42,0:34:38.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么在地球上 如此巨大的植食动物是如何 在这个寸草不生的地方生存的呢\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So how on earth does a plant-eater this size survive in a place apparently totally devoid of vegetation?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.02,0:34:48.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,纳米比亚的大象是非洲最能吃苦的动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Elephants in Namibia are the toughest in Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.02,0:34:50.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们必须如此\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And they need to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.30,0:35:10.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,仅有的少量食物也非常分散\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}What little food exists is so dispersed
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.54,0:35:13.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这些大象每天得走上50英里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}that these elephants walk up to 50 miles a day
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.66,0:35:18.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沿着干涸的河床搜寻一些可以吃的东西\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}as they travel up the dry river channels searching for something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.34,0:35:37.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时这个愿望看起来根本不可能实现\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At times the task looks truly helpless.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.66,0:36:14.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大象似乎不属于有这种地形的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Elephants may seem out of place in this landscape,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.38,0:36:16.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它们并非唯一意外的物种\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but they're not the only ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.70,0:36:36.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,奇怪的是 狮子也生活在这里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Amazingly, lions live here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.54,0:36:47.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,热带大草原的竞争促使鼎盛的 狮群数量达到20只 甚至更多\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In savanah country huge herds of games support prides containing 20 lions or more.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.26,0:36:51.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而若想在此生存  狮子必须改变它们的习性\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But to live here lions have had to change their habits -
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.10,0:36:52.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狮群规模小了很多\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}prides are much smaller
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.66,0:36:55.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但家族的疆土面积却大大增加\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and their home ranges are very much bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.66,0:36:59.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里还有另一个问题\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And there's an added problem -
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.38,0:37:03.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的食物总是在移动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}their food is always on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.10,0:37:13.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和大象一样\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Like the elephants,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.46,0:37:18.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狮子也必须长途跋涉 寻找生存所需的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the lions must travel great distances to find enough to live on.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.94,0:37:35.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是狮子并不是什么地方都能去的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But lions can't go everywhere -
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.62,0:37:39.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们不会试着爬过一座沙丘\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they won't attempt to cross this field of sand dunes
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.90,0:37:42.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,长角羚很清楚这一点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the oryx know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.26,0:38:43.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狮子必须耐心等待 长角羚离开安全的沙丘\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The lions must wait for the oryx to leave the safety of the dunes,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.34,0:38:46.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它们最后总得寻找食物和水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}which eventually they must to find food and water.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.22,0:38:48.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,介时狮子就能伏击它们\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And then the lions will ambush them.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.62,0:39:55.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大象找到了一些它们最喜欢吃的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The elephants have found some of their favourite food.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.26,0:40:05.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,草是所有大象的主食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Grasses are the staple diet of all elephants,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.22,0:40:08.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但这群象却忙着挖掘草根\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but this herd concentrates on digging up the roots,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.58,0:40:12.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为草根中的营养和水分比茎干多得多\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}which have more nutrition and moisture than the stems.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.66,0:40:17.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这一举措在这个资源 严重匮乏的地方显得极为重要\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's the sort of behaviour that can make all the difference in a place of serious shortages.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.94,0:40:22.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而所有这一切即刻就将发生改变\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Yet all this can change in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.02,0:40:43.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,许多沙漠的命运都由远方的雨水决定\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The fortunes of many deserts are ruled by distant rains.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.74,0:40:48.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些水来自100英里之外的山地降雨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This water fell as rain in mountains more than a hundred miles away.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.14,0:40:55.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它叫做“瞬时洪水”\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's known as a flash flood
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.02,0:41:00.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,之所以这么叫是因为 这些水可能仅仅流淌一天左右\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and called that because the water may run for just a single day.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.38,0:41:04.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且一年最多也只发生1～2次\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's an event that only happens once or twice a year at the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.86,0:41:29.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,布满沙子的河床像是一张巨大的吸水纸\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The sandy riverbed acts like a giant strip of blotting paper
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.22,0:41:32.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,水一边流淌一边被它吸去\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}sucking up the water as soon as it appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.50,0:41:44.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里的每一寸土壤都已被河水润湿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But every square metre of soil moistened by this river
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.82,0:41:49.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为生活在这里的动物们带来了生机\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}will increase the chances of survival for those that live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.54,0:41:57.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,水坑里暂时填满了水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Waterholes are filled temprorarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.26,0:42:05.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非洲其它地方的大象每天都会喝水\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Elsewhere in Africa elephants drink every day,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.66,0:42:07.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但这里缺水的现状\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the lack of water here
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.34,0:42:13.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,意味着沙漠里的大象 只能每隔四五天喝饱一回\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}means that desert elephants can only refill their tanks once every four or five days.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.86,0:42:19.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,短短一周内 瞬时洪水浸润过的 土地上已长出了青草\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Within a week the flash flood has produced a flush of green,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.10,0:42:22.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,远远多于从沙丘返回的长角羚的需求\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}more than enough to draw the oryx out of the dunes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.10,0:42:29.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是它们仅有的积累食物储备的机会\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's a rare chance for them to build up their food reserves.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.30,0:42:41.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,洪水也让狮子过上了好日子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The flood has made life easier for the lions, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.86,0:42:48.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这只长角羚的肉最多 能维持整个家族一星期左右\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The flesh of this oryx will keep the family going for a week at the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.86,0:42:54.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此时 狩猎暂时变得容易许多  河道也穿上了一件绿装\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But for a while the hunting will be easier, now that river channel has turned green.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.10,0:43:01.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,狮子和长角羚的美好时光十分短暂\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The good times for lions and oryx are brief,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.10,0:43:07.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但就是这些短暂的日子使它们 得以全年在沙漠中生活\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but these are the short moments that make it possible to live in deserts the year round.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.02,0:43:16.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,死亡谷是地球上最热的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Death Valley is the hottest place on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.10,0:43:20.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而这个“火炉”也会因为水而发生改变\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Yet even this furnace can be transformed by water.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.34,0:43:37.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一场大雨使得在地下沉睡了30多年的 种子迸发出生命的活力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A single shower can enable seeds that have lain dormant for 30 years or more to burst into life.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.30,0:43:49.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里已有一个世纪 没有像现在这样开满鲜花\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And there hasn't been a bloom like this one for a century.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.34,0:44:04.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,死亡谷中的花期很短\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The periods of boom in Death Valley are short.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.86,0:44:09.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它们发生的次数 足以保证生命长盛不衰\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but they're just frequent enough to keep life ticking over.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.22,0:44:21.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,植物的突然兴盛是 所有沙漠动物都盼望的事\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A sudden flush of vegetation is what every desert dweller waits for,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.78,0:44:24.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦发生 它们必须尽可能地利用它\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and when it happens they must make the most of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.50,0:44:49.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好日子到来时 地球上没有其它物种\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There is no other species on the planet that responds
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.00,0:44:52.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能像沙漠蝗那样迅速而又戏剧性地作出反应\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}as quickly and as dramatically to the good times as the desert locust.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.90,0:44:58.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在地下埋藏了20年的虫卵开始孵化\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Eggs that have remained in the ground for 20 years begin to hatch.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.86,0:45:13.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沙漠蝗的若虫是跳跃能手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The young locusts are known as hoppers,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.02,0:45:15.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这一阶段 它们还不能飞\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}for at this stage they're flightless.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.62,0:45:21.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们循着萌发的草香寻找新的用餐场所\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They find new feeding grounds by following the smell of sprouting grass.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.54,0:45:31.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一般说来 若虫需要 经过4周才能变成成虫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Normally it takes four weeks for hoppers to become adults,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.34,0:45:33.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但如果条件允许 譬如现在\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but when the conditions are right as now
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.86,0:45:37.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的生长过程就会切换到快车道\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}their development switches to the fast track.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.38,0:45:45.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当一个地方的植物即将吃光时\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the vegetation in one place begins to run out
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.54,0:45:48.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,长着翅膀的成虫便释放出信息素  即一些气味信号\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the winged adults release pheromones - scent messages,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.98,0:45:52.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,提醒蝗群中的其它成员它们应该动身了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}which tell others in the group that they must move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.86,0:46:05.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蝗群合并之后\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And when groups merge,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.58,0:46:08.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,形成了一团蝗虫云\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they form a swarm.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.38,0:46:33.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成虫每天的进食量相当于自己的体重\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}An adult locust eats its entire body weight every day,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.42,0:46:38.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而整团蝗虫云能消耗掉数百吨植物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and a whole swarm can consume literally hundreds of tonnes of vegetation.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.30,0:46:42.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们必须不停地迁徙\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They have to keep on moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.90,0:46:46.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沙漠蝗御风而行\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The swarm travels with the wind -
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.10,0:46:49.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是最省力的飞行方式\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it's the most energy-saving way of flying.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.82,0:46:58.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着风向迁徙意味着 它们总是飞向低压地区\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Following the flow of wind means that they're always heading toward areas of low pressure,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.26,0:47:03.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里正是风雨交加的地方 植物定能生长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}places where wind meets rain and vegetation starts to grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.26,0:47:06.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在飞行过程中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As they fly,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.34,0:47:08.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一团蝗虫云也会和其它蝗虫云汇合\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}swarms join up with other swarms
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.90,0:47:15.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从而形成巨大的灾害  无数“瘟神”组成的大军绵延长达40英里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to form gigantic plagues several billions strong and as much as 40 miles wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.22,0:47:21.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们将把一路上能吃的东西 全部吃得精光\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They will consume every edible thing that lies in their path.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.54,0:47:38.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是地球上最壮观的景象之一\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is one of planet Earth's greatest spectacles.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.54,0:47:40.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很少能看见如此大的规模\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's rarely seen on this scale
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.66,0:47:42.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且也不会持续多久\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and it won't last long.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.70,0:47:44.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,待到食物耗尽之时\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Once the food is gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.46,0:47:49.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,无数蝗虫拍打翅膀时的喧哗将不复存在\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the steady roar of a billion beating locust wings will once again
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.00,0:47:54.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,再次取代它的只是沙漠中呼啸的风声\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}be replaced by nothing more than the sound of the desert wind.

